<ol start="3" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>CESSATION OF SERVICES</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>This appointment and employment with the Company will be governed as under:</p>
<ul>
  <li>You will be on probation for a period of<strong> three months</strong> from the date of your joining. During this period your services can be terminated without any notice
    period and without any compensation incase, your performance is considered as unsatisfactory by the company. <br/></li>
  <li>After the satisfactory completion of the probation period based on the satisfactory results of a complete background and reference check carried out by the Company, your
    services will be confirmed and a notice period of 30 days or an equivalent salary thereof will be required from either side for the cessation (resignation or termination) of
    your services from the company.
  </li>
</ul>
<ol start="4" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>WORK-WEEK, LEAVE AND HOLIDAYS</strong></li>
</ol>
<ul>
  <li>The Company will observe six days a week. However, in the interest of company&rsquo;s activities you may have to work extra hours to ensure that critical/urgent work is
    completed satisfactorily within the target/ prescribed time period.
  </li>
  <li>The Company may at its sole discretion and as it deems fit, depute you wherever your services are required. You will be required to offer your services as an employee at a
    location specified by the Company within the time span of 8am to 8pm for a shift timing of 8 hours.
  </li>
  <li>Leave: You will be entitled to the holidays and leaves as per the company&rsquo;s policy.</li>
</ul>

<ol start="5" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>CODE OF CONDUCT</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>You will be governed by the Company's Service Rulesthat are prevalent or will be made from time-to-time. You will also be required to abide by the Code of Conduct of the
  Company.</p>
<ol start="6" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>COMPANY PROPERTY</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>You will be responsible for the safekeeping and return in good condition and order all Company property which is in your possession, use, custody or charge. You shall make good
  of any loss or damage that occurs to any Company property which is in your possession/ custody.</p>
<ol start="7" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>ACCOUNTABILITY</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>You are required to adhere to all the Company policies and procedures, whether written or oral, and always act in the best interests of the Company.</p>
<ol start="8" class="ol_one_padding">
  <li><strong>ABSENCE</strong></li>
</ol>
<p>Any unauthorized absence for a continuous period of six days (including your over-staying the period of leave) would automatically make you lose your lien on the service, and
  your services shall automatically and forthwith stand terminated by the Company without any notice or any compensation in lieu of such notice.</p>
